commit.message: Prepare 1.4.3 release

Fix up test_pipeline_move test for older redis-py

Older versions would skip issuing a transaction if it had no commands,
even if there were watches.

Make unit tests pass against redis 5.x again

A recently-added test was for a Redis 6.0 feature (KEEPTTL), and failed
when run against a 5.0 server. I generalised the code used for the
test_pipeline_move test to allow skipping tests based on a minimum
server version.

Make MOVE invalidate watches again

Originally 187fcd7 changed MOVE so that it wouldn't invalidate watches,
for compatibility with redis 5.0. However, 6.0 fixed that in redis, so
restore the original behaviour.

Also add a unit test that gets skipped when run against redis < 6.0.

Closes #279.

commit.message: Update documentation on running the tests

Some cleanups

- Mark tests with pytest.mark.real/fake so that they can be selected.
- Make a `@fake_only` alias to reduce copy-paste.
- Convert TestPubSubConnected to use pytest fixtures.
- Put pytest.mark.asyncio at module level to avoid repetition

Use async_generator package for test_aioredis

The previous approach of using event_loop.run_until_complete wasn't
working with newer versions of Python.
Remove duplicated fixture
Remove unused import
